<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">
<br>
Replay controls allows the viewer to display images which have been
buffered in the camera.  The number of previous images available to
view depends on the capacity of the CF card in the camera and the size
of the images.

<br><br>
Click on the rewind button to play backwards.  Clicking more
than once increases playback speed.

<br><br>
Click on pause to pause playback.  Click it again to resume play.

<br><br>
Click on the fastforward button to fast forward.  Clicking more
than once increases playback speed.

<br><br>
The slider handle can be dragged to change the playback location.  The ends of the slider bar indicate the earliest and newest image times.

<br><br>
Click on the size up button to toggle the playback size.

<br><br>
Click on the "SNAPSHOT" button to save an image.

<br><br>
Click on the "VIDEO CLIP" button to save a video clip as an AVI file.

<br><br>
Zoom in by left clicking in the image.  Zoom out by right clicking.  Recenter by clicking the middle mouse button.

